           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-5">Gho Kan-in, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanra, Tai Kan-as, Tai Panpo, Tai Kaṁphac, Tai Kaṁpit, Tai Vñau, Gho Śrīneta. Total: 7 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied> and 7 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; grand total 14.</p>
              <p n="5-11">Sruk Virendrapattana: Gho Kanmar, Gho Kaṁpañ, Gho Kanlāt, Gho Kanteṅ, Gvāl Ajāya, Gvāl Thleṁ, Tai Laṅgāy, Tai Kan-hey, Tai Kanteṅ, Tai Kaṁvis accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied> Vara, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/></p>
